insert into "books" ("description", "image_url", "title") values ('NEW EDITION, REVISED AND UPDATED When it comes to creating ideas, we hold ourselves back. That‚Äôs because inside each of us is an internal editor whose job is to forever polish our thoughts so we sound smart and in control and so we fit into society. But what happens when we encounter problems where such conventional thinking fails us? How do we get unstuck? For Mark Levy, the answer is freewriting, a technique he‚Äôs used for years to solve all types of business problems and generate ideas for books, articles, and blog posts. Freewriting is deceptively simple: start writing as fast as you can, for as long as you can, about a subject you care deeply about, while ignoring the standard rules of grammar and spelling. Your internal editor won‚Äôt be able to keep up with your output‚Äîyou‚Äôll generate breakthrough ideas and solutions that you couldn‚Äôt have created any other way. Levy shares his six secrets to freewriting as well as fifteen problem-solving and creativity-stimulating principles you can use if you need more firepower‚Äîseven of which are new to this edition. Also new to this edition: an extensive section on how to refine your raw freewriting into something you can share with the world.', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=h3bEkR-n9NoC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Accidental Genius');
